hopobject.body: Could you ask her to call me? prescription drugs help with cost Although Lotus created a special sealed body, Perry Oceanographics still had a lot of work to do, and the overall cost to construct the car was more than $100,000 – the equivalent of almost $500,000 (Â£325,000) today. In a classic case of movie magic, Wet Nellie's interior bears no relation to what is seen in the film – in place of the standard cabin it had a simple platform seat for the driver, while an unsightly mass of motors, batteries, levers and pipes were used to propel and manoeuvre it.
